## 2. The OCaml implementation (`pcapng.ml`)

Only a few tiny wrappers are needed – everything else lives in the C‑stub.

```ocaml
(* pcapng.ml – thin wrappers around the C stubs *)

type t = private unit   (* abstract – the real representation lives in C *)

type frame = {
  ts   : float;
  data : bytes;
}

external open_file : string -> t = "pcapng_open"
external close     : t -> unit = "pcapng_close"
external iter      : (frame -> unit) -> t -> unit = "pcapng_iter"
external next      : t -> frame option = "pcapng_next"
external reset     : t -> unit = "pcapng_reset"
```

